# Database Rules

## Clients

- Server Components / Route Handlers: `lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Client Components: `lib/supabase/client.ts`
- Privileged jobs only: `lib/supabase/admin.ts` (`service_role`, bypasses RLS) — API routes, Edge, payout engine
- Never import admin into Client Components or any browser bundle (`server-only` enforced)
- Access DB only through typed Supabase clients — no raw SQL strings in components

## Schema

Before assuming column names, check `lib/supabase/types.ts`.

| Table | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `profiles` | Marketing accounts (slug, commission_rate) |
| `landing_pages` | Puck pages at `/l/{profile}/{landing}` |
| `visits` | Pageviews (session_id, referrer, device) |
| `leads` | Form submissions (session_id, bitrix_lead_id) |
| `payout_periods` | Per-profile payout windows |

Types: PascalCase (`Profile`, `Landing`, `Visit`, `Lead`). Tables: snake_case.

## Queries

Always select explicit columns — never `.select('*')` in production.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const { data } = await supabase.from('leads').select('*')

// ✅ GOOD
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('leads')
  .select('id, session_id, bitrix_lead_id, deal_value, converted_at')
```

## Security

- Hash IPs (SHA-256) before storage — never store raw IPs
- Do not put Supabase `service_role` key in client components
- Enable RLS on all tables used from the browser; use anon/publishable key there
